<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F77DB13CB182FA5832C246FC" box="[199,251,1447,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: Sundevall referred to characters of both male and female in his original description, and according to his acquisition catalogue, he had at least 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF77DB13CB3A6FA3431B546A7" box="[739,908,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
available at the time. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F77DB13CB5CDFA3437A546A7" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[1160,1436,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 83)</bibRefCitation>
